article.headline: Boise State 82, Oregon State 80
article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Boise State guard Ryan Defares scored 25 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, leading his team to an 82-80 win over Oregon State Saturday. The Broncos, 4-0 on the road, improved to 8-1 and 6-22 all-time against Pac-10 teams. Bronco guard Jermaine Blackburn added 16 points and forward Aaron Haynes tipped in 13. The Beavers dropped to 4-4 and were led by forward Jim Hanchett with 18 points and eight rebounds off the bench. Guard Chris Stephens added 16 points. "We made the big plays and the right plays at the right time," said Boise State coach Greg Graham. Of Defares, he said, "Down the stretch he was making some big plays." Oregon State was ahead 41-40 at halftime but Boise State continued to keep it close until OSU guard Lamar Hurd hit a lay-in and was fouled giving the Beavers a 78-74 lead with 3:38 left. The Broncos outscored OSU 8-2 in the remaining time. Defares missed two three-throws with 1 second left but Stephens' layin missed and the Broncos ran out the clock. OSU opens Pac-10 play at UCLA Jan. 2. Boise State took advantage of poor OSU first-half shooting to make an 18-4 run and get a 20-8 lead. Oregon State hit just three of its first 14 shots. Haines got seven points during the run. "We can compete physically, but mentally, I don't know what it is," Hurd said after the game. "As soon as we cut that out we're going to be fine." Of Stephens' last missed shot, Hanchett said, "Chris has done it before so obviously we're confident in him. Sometimes the ball just doesn't fall the way you plan it.'
